<HEADLINE> UN Warns S. Leone Rebels of Confrontation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 4 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations peacekeeping force
in Sierra Leone warned on Thursday that the recent attacks on UN
troops by rebels could lead to violent confrontations between the
two sides.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference in the west African country's capital
Freetown, the UN force also accused the rebels of the
Revolutionary United Front (RUF) of completely destroying
disarmament camps in the country's central towns of Makeni and
Magburaka, in addition to taking dozens of UN personnel hostage
and killing of its soldiers.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the UN force said that there had been sporadic
gun shots on Wednesday night in the capital Freetown.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, RUF leader Foday Sankoh made a broadcast message
Wednesday promising "immediate measures" to free the detainees.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
