<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Canal Toll Revenue Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Panama Canal toll revenues
dropped 0.7 percent during the first six months of the 2000 fiscal
year from October 1999 to March,  compared to the same period of
the previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
A communique issued Friday by the Panama Canal Authority (ACP)
says that the entity obtained 292.7 million U.S. dollar toll fees
during the period, while it was 294.9 million dollars during the
previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The communique shows that a total o 6,221 ships traversed the
interoceanic waterway during the period, about 34 ships per day,
reducing by 4.6 percent compared to the same period of the 1998-
1999 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
However, revenue as well as the number of transits surpassed
the ACP forecasts, which took over the administration of the
waterway on December 31, 1999, of 288.1 million dollars and 5,521
ships, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
