<HEADLINE> Colombian Army Kills Eight Guerrilla Fighters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A confrontation between Colombian
Army soldiers and rebel guerrilla fighters in rural zones of the
Cauca department in the southwest of the country left eight rebels
dead Friday, military authorities said.
</P>
<P>
The rebel casualties, four men and four women, belonged to the
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) Seventh Front,
according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The army and the guerrillas combated in a spot of the central
Andean range, while the army is in hot pursuit of guerrillas who
flee over the mountains near the Timbio municipality. 
</P>
