<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romanian Invention to Revolutionize Flying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Romanian engineer Grigore Nica
from Bucharest has invented an aircraft whose design can
revolutionize flying, the daily Libertatea reported in its Friday
issue.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft is a disc, looking like a "classical" UFO, able to
take off easily even if it is very big and very heavy. The
inventor said the ship can remain suspended in the air regardless
of the altitude, it can move also on the vertical and easily enter
the outer space, and its speed can increase progressively,
continuously and virtually indefinitely.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft works according to the principle of annulling the
gravitational force by the centrifugal force, by energy build-up
in the edges. Not only the performance but also the structure are
similar to a UFO's in science fiction.
</P>
<P>
The ship is composed of three functionally interdependent discs,
with a common symmetry axis and the barycenters on the same
vertical axis.
</P>
<P>
The author of the invention said he established the technical
data of the design as early as 1987 but was afraid then to make
public his invention. Not long ago he decided to present the
design to Romtehnica corporation, specialized in foreign trade
with military equipment and services. The file was subsequently
tabled with the State Office for Inventions and Trade Marks, for
getting a license.
</P>
<P>
According to the daily Libertatea, a document signed by
Romtehnica managers, both the National Defense Ministry and the
Agency of Research for Military Technologies showed interest in
the invention. The specialists of these institutions believe the
theory in question is correct. The sizes are being calculated for
the building of a prototype. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
