<HEADLINE> European Countries at Top of Foreign Investments in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The European countries have the
highest percentage in the foreign investments made in Romania in
the past ten years, the daily Curentul reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
As many as 73,489 companies in which foreign capital was put
were registered in Romania between December 1990 - March 2000,
with 4.5 billion U.S. dollars as the nominal capital invested in
hard currency.
</P>
<P>
As much as 78.6 percent of the foreign investments in Romania
are investments by European countries, which amount to 3.57
billion U.S. dollars Asian countries come next, with 480 million U.
S. dollars, or 10.5 percent, followed by countries in the North
American continent, with 400 million U.S. dollars, or 8.8 percent,
countries in South America, 1.1 percent, African countries, 0.5
percent and countries in Oceania, 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to statistical data, 779 companies in which foreign
capital was put were created in Romania in March this year. Of the
total nominal capital subscribed by the newly created firms, which
stands at 14.4 million U.S. dollars, 97.7 percent comes from
European countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
