the deaths of an 80-year-old woman and her 40-year-old daughter and
Israel's earlier air strikes against the Lebanese civilian targets
which wounded at least 12 Lebanese.
</P>
<P>
The Israelis are trying to make up for their failure in
realizing their expansionist policies on the eve of withdrawal of
their troops from south Lebanon, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Expressing concern over the continuation of Israeli raids
against Lebanese people, Asefi called for the international
community to use every possible means to stop the Israeli assaults.
</P>
<P>
Israel, which Iran has refused to recognize and termed as a
threat in the region, has announced to withdraw from south Lebanon
where it set a self-claimed security zone to safeguard northern
Israel from guerilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah, or Party of God supported by Iran and Syria, has been
spearheading a resistance war to end Israeli occupation in south
Lebanon. 
