Annan Friday deplored the escalation of violence between Israel
and Lebanon guerrillas and urged both sides to desist from further
violence.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by his spokesman's office said "the
secretary-general deplores the escalation around Lebanon since
last Wednesday that has caused casualties among civilians on both
sides, including the death of two Lebanese women."
</P>
<P>
"He calls on both sides to desist from further violence and in
particular to cease all attacks on civilians and civilian
infrastructure," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Fighting intensified Friday when Israeli warplanes struck
targets across Lebanon and Hizbollah guerrillas launched a new
barrage of missiles into northern Israel.
</P>
<P>
The exchanges of fire came as U.N. Special Envoy on the Middle
East Terje Roed-Larsen was visiting Lebanon to discuss plans for
Israel's complete withdrawal by July from southern Lebanon.
