<DOCNO> XIE20000505.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania President Promulgates Anti-Corruption Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu signed the decree regarding the promulgation of the
law of preventing, finding and sanctioning corruption, said the
presidential institution Friday.
</P>
<P>
The law, which sets up measures of preventing, finding and
sanctioning corruption, is directed to certain categories of
people, mainly, those who carry out a public office within public
institutions.
</P>
<P>
The law is directed to people who control or who offer
specialty assistance to the extent to which they participate in
the decision making process or they can influence these decisions
in the public institutions. The law is also directed to people who
are involved in bank, hard currency exchange, credit, or bank
account operations as well as to people who hold a leadership
office in a party or a political formation, a trade union, an
employer's organization or a foundation.
</P>
<P>
The law establishes the categories of offenses and strengthens
the sanction system that is stipulated in the penal code. 
</P>
</TEXT>
