<HEADLINE> 150,000 Angolans Suffer from AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Angola has an estimated150,000 people
 suffering from AIDS, accounting for 1.4 percent of the population
of the southwest African country, a senior government health
official said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"When I say we have an estimated 150,000 cases, I mean that
this is the number we should have registered if our health
services worked satisfactorily countrywide," said the director of
the national anti-AIDS campaign, Dulcelina Serrano.
</P>
<P>
Given the lack of proper health facilities across much of the
war-torn country, only 5,764 cases of AIDS had been officially
registered by February, with Cabinda province, a northwest
enclave, and the areas around the capital Luanda, showing the
highest rates, Serrano said.
</P>
<P>
She said the major form of transmission was through
heterosexual contact.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
