<HEADLINE> British Child Pornography Suspect Commits Suicide in Holland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A British man suspected of
production of child pornography has committed suicide in an
Amsterdam police station, Dutch press reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch newspaper De Volkskrant said that the 42-year-old man,
who was not identified, hanged himself in an interrogation cell
before police officers could interview him.
</P>
<P>
The report said the man was arrested after he left a photo
development shop in Amsterdam but had not been officially taken
into police custody. For personal safety reasons, the man had had
his shoelaces and belt taken away by police.
</P>
<P>
Friday is a public holiday in the Netherlands. Neither police
officers nor British embassy staff could be reached for comment on
details of the incident. 
</P>
