<HEADLINE> Three Blasts Rock Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 5 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was killed and
six others injured when three blasts rocked Pakistan's southern
port city of Karachi on Friday, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
All the three blasts were aimed at police buildings of the city,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
One person was killed and four others were injured by a bomb
planted in a motorcycle parked outside the office of a senior
district police officer in eastern Karachi, the police said.
</P>
