<HEADLINE> Cooperation With NGOs Crucial in Poverty Reduction: ADB Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHIANG MAI, Thailand, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Closer cooperation with
non-government organization (NGO) is a critical part of the Asian
Development Bank's (ADB) fight against poverty, ADB President
Tadao Chino said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting with NGO members, Chino said over half
the ADB's projects approved in 1999 involved NGOs in some
substantial way, adding that NGO's involvement in the development
of ADB's country assistance plans for the developing members also
increased significantly.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said he had ordered that a comprehensive review of
ADB's overall programs of cooperation with NGOs be undertaken and
finished within this year.
</P>
<P>
The review will aim at strengthening existing relations with
NGOs and developing new ones. "I would like to see the level of
cooperation between ADB and NGOs further increase in the future,"
said Chino.
</P>
<P>
He also reiterated that the ADB's poverty reduction strategy "
calls for closer cooperation with NGOs through effective
consultation and cooperation in new reduction initiatives."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the ADB is very interested in learning NGO's
views and concerns and wants to continue dialogue and consultation
with NGOs and civil society.
</P>
<P>
ADB is going to hold an open forum on cooperation between ADB
and NGOs here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 33rd Annual Meeting of the Board of Governors of the ADB is
going to be held in this mountainous city, some 1,000 kilometers
north of Bangkok, from Saturday to Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
