<HEADLINE> Philippines to Host ASEAN Labor Ministers' Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government announced
Friday that it will host the 14th ASEAN (Association of Southeast
Asian Nations) Labor Ministers' Meeting (ALMM) to be held on May
11-12.
</P>
<P>
Labor Secretary Bienvenido Laguesma said President Joseph
Estrada is expected to address the ALMM which will be preceded by
the 7th ASEAN Sub-Committee on Labor Affairs Meeting (ASCLAM) on
May 9 and the Senior Labor Officials Meeting (SLOM) on May 10.
</P>
<P>
Laguema said in a statement the ministerial meeting will be
attended by 10 labor ministers from Brunei Darussalam, Cambodia,
Laos, Indonesia Malaysia, Myanmar, Philippines, Singapore,
Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
As a prelude to the ALMM, ASCLAM and SLOM meetings, a strategic
planning workshop was held on April 10-12 in the southern
Philippine city of Cebu.
</P>
<P>
The workshop sought to develop a five-year program of action to
assist the ASEAN labor ministers in formulating and strengthening
policies for social protection, employment and income generation
and promotion of social cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines is one of the five founding members of the
ASEAN, an economic common market that was formed on August 8, 1967.
</P>
