<HEADLINE> China to Build Motorcycle Assembly Line in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- China will build the first motorcycle
assembly line in Angola, with a total investment of 7.2 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Guangdong Overseas Construction Corporation (GOCC)
presented here on Friday 10 samples of motorcycles to the Angolan
Industrial Ministry, kicking off the bilateral cooperation in the
assembly of motorcycles in Angola.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Angola Jiang Yuande attended the handover
ceremony, saying this symbolic gesture not only constitutes one
more proof of the solidarity and fraternity between the two
countries but also shows the good perspective of the future
cooperation in the assembly of motorcycles in Luanda.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang Fengzhong, head of the GOCC delegation,
Angola is a big potential market for motorcycles although the
country is currently suffering civil conflicts.
</P>
<P>
China is considered by African countries as a good example in
the development of national economy and has good experience and
technology that are practical and useful for African countries,
said Angolan Industrial Minister Albina Assis at the ceremony.
</P>
