<HEADLINE> EU Pledges More Aid for Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission on Friday
announced an offer of an additional 67.5 million euros (62.7
million U.S. dollars) for reconstruction and rehabilitation in
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
The move has brought to 73.5 million euros (68.3 million
dollars) worth of European Union humanitarian aid to the African
country since the February floods there.
</P>
<P>
The EU pledge met 15 percent of the aid appealed by the
Mozambique authorities for reconstruction and rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
"This is the most tangible and meaningful manner by which the
European Commission can help the people of Mozambique rebuild
their lives and economy," said EU Humanitarian Commissioner Poul
Nielson.
</P>
<P>
In last February, Mozambique was struck by torrential rainfalls
and following cyclones, which together triggered devastating
flooding affecting the country's extensive areas.
</P>
<P>
The EU's executive body said its new offer will fund projects
of flood protection, rebuilding of transport and rural
telecommunications systems, basic social services and public
health in Mozambique. 
</P>
</TEXT>
