<HEADLINE> Industrial Producer Prices up in EU, Euro Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The industrial producer price index
rose in both the European Union and the euro zone in March this
year, Eurostat reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical office of the European
Community said that the industrial producer prices went up in
March by 0.5 percent compared with the previous month while the
prices rose by 0.6 percent in the euro zone in the same period of
time.
</P>
<P>
For the 15-nation union and the 11-nation single currency club,
the industrial producer price index posted the same increase in
February, Eurostat said.
</P>
<P>
As in previous months, the March increase was led by the index
for intermediate goods that rose by 0.8 percent in the EU and by 0.
9 percent in the euro zone.
</P>
<P>
Compared with March last year, the industrial producer prices
were up by 5.6 percent in the European Union and by 6.2 percent in
the euro zone.
</P>
<P>
The increase again stemmed mainly from the intermediate goods
sector. The prices rose much less in other sectors, although the
annual rate of most of them has edged slightly up in the past six
months, Eurostat said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
