<HEADLINE> Uganda, Rwanda Clash In DRC, Kills Five </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan and Rwandan forces fought
each other outside the rebel-held Kisangani in the eastern part
of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) on Friday, according
to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
At least five civilians died and nine others wounded in the
clash, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Shaban Bantariza, Ugandan army spokesman, refused to confirmed
the clash in a telephone interview with Xinhua. But he said
further information might be available later.
</P>
<P>
Uganda and Rwanda have been close allies for years in the
Congolese conflict. Tensions have steadily increased between the
two allies since march 1999 for they are backing rival rebel
forces in the DRC. Both Uganda and Rwanda have in recent weeks
reportedly reinforced their forces stationed near Kisangani, the
third largest city in the DRC. Rwanda accused Uganda was massing
troops in the same area recently.
</P>
<P>
The two estranged allies staged massive offensives against each
other in Kisangani In August 1999. 
