<HEADLINE> Passenger Arrivals in Macao Rise 26 Pct in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Passenger arrivals in Macao via sea,
land and air routes exceeded 720,500 in March this year, a sharp
increase of 26.1 percent over the same month of 1999, the latest
official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Passenger arrivals from China's Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR), the mainland and Taiwan accounted for
52.1 percent, 28.4 percent and 12.7 percent respectively,
according to figures released by the Statistics and Census
Services of the Macao SAR government.
</P>
<P>
In the first three months of the year, passenger arrivals in
Macao were nearly 2.2 million, a rise of 22.9 percent over the
same quarter last year.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the number of passengers from Hong Kong rose 11.
1 percent, and those from the mainland areas of China and the
Republic of Korea showed considerable growth of 66.1 percent and
43.1 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
