Korea have not reflected yet the potentialities of the two
countries,"Shihab said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Han Duck-soo reiterated South Korean government's
commitment to strongly supporting the on-going economic recovery
program in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
"On this occasion I would like to make it very clear that the
South Korean government and the country's businessmen have a
strong faith in the ability of the Indonesian government and they
will work together,"Han Duck-soo said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia and South Korea have close economic relations. The
volume of trade between the two countries increased from 4 billion
U.S. dollars in 1998 to 4.6 billion dollars in 1999. 
