<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket finished
with a 50-point rise Friday.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed up 49.7 points or 1.6 percent
to 3,075.6, almost erasing Thursday's 50.8-point decline. New
market benchmark, the ASX200, closed up 53.4 points to 3,107.2.
</P>
<P>
Banks were strong following the solid half-year results
announced by the ANZ, Westpac and NAB this week.
</P>
<P>
Westpac shares jumped 52 cents to 10.95 Australian dollars as
it posted a 16.7 percent lift in its net profit to 818 million
Australian dollars (476.98 million U.S. dollars) for the half-year
to March 31, 2000.
</P>
<P>
NAB was up 83.6 cents to 24.47 Australian dollars, ANZ lifted
28.1 cents to 11.641 Australian dollars and Commonwealth shares
increased by 70.2 cents to 26.302 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
The media sector was mostly higher. News Corp ordinary shares
were up 50 cents to 21.20 Australian dollars. Publishing &AMP;
Broadcasting was up 13.4 cents to 12.117 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Telstra continued to fall Friday. Its shares remain 18-month
lows, down another three cents to 6.95 Australian dollars. C&AMP;W
Optus fell two cents to 5.28 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was a volume of 442.3 million shares trading
1.185 billion Australian dollars (600.10 million U.S. dollars).
There were 810 rising stocks, 607 falling and 440 were steady.
</P>
