<DOCNO> XIE20000505.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hke050556 --Indonesian Gov't to Sign Peace Accord With Aceh Separatists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The government of Indonesia and the
Acehnese separatist group (GAM) are planning to sign a memorandum
of understanding (MoU) on the reduction of tension and violence in
country's Aceh province, a senior official said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in a press conference here, Foreign
Minister Alwi Shihab said the MoU is due to be signed in Geneva,
Switzerland on May 12, by the Indonesian government permanent
representative there,Ambassador Hasan Wirayuda and the GAM
representatives.
</P>
<P>
"In principle, we want to solve the Aceh problem, but not its
territorial issues but just the problem of the Acehnese who are
now suffering due to contracted conflict between the separatists
and the central government. We want to focus our talks with the
GAM in Geneva on how to help the Acehnese people and stop their
misery," Shihab said.
</P>
<P>
The main substance of the agreement is not to continue the
violence but to lay down weapons, a government official said
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Shihab said the international community has given their support
to Indonesia to defend its territory from disintegration threats.
</P>
<P>
The GAM, an underground armed group in the western-most
province of Indonesia has been fighting for 25 years to demand an
Acehnese independence.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of civilians and military officers as well as
separatist members died in the conflicts.
</P>
<P>
"There is no problem with integrity of territory in Indonesia,
including Aceh province (it will remain Indonesia's province). We
are not going to talk about political issues in Geneva,"Shihab
said.
</P>
<P>
He further said that with the signing of the MoU, both sides
are expected to agree to reduce tension and violence in the
predominantly Moslem province of Aceh.
</P>
<P>
"We also hope that we are going to find a best solution to
resolve the Acehnese issue. We always give priority to a dialogue
measure in this point," Sihab said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
