<HEADLINE> Shares Prices Dip on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gave up 2.44 points to
end at 2,118.36 points in active trading.
</P>
<P>
The total volume swelled to 696.76 million shares worth 544.40
million Singapore dollars (about 316.27 million U.S. dollars).
Advancing issues outnumbered declining counters by 193 to 154 with
191 other stocks unchanged.
</P>
<P>
AirOcean topped the volume list as it registered a turnover of
81.70 million units. Medi-Rad was the second most heavily traded
stock with 70.78 million shares transacted. It was followed by
GiantWTech which had 53.05 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 headed ascent of the day running up 120 cents to
close at 44.20 Singapore dollars. ShangAsia rose by 75 cents to
finish at 8.95 Hong Kong dollars. UOB climbed by 30 cents to end
at 11.70 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Venture gave up 80 cents to finish at 19.80 Singapore dollars.
Chartered and PacCent fell by 50 cents each to end at 11.80 and 14.
70 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said shares ended the day on a mixed note in active
trading with a small group of healthcare stocks, the closest
biotechnology issues here, were chased higher on speculative plays.
</P>
<P>
They said that despite the soft tone the level of trading
activity appeared to have picked up in the final trading session
of the week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
