<HEADLINE> Death Toll Rises to 18 in Earthquake in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the Antara News Agency Friday, 10 of the deceased
were residents of Bangkep regency and eight others were from
Banggai regency.
</P>
<P>
A tectonic earthquake measuring 6.5 on the Richter scale jolted
the Banggai islands on Thursday. The epicenter of the earthquake
was in the Peleng strait, some 2,000 kilometers northeast of
Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers have been unable so far to reach more isolated areas
and there were fears the death toll could rise, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that huge waves triggered by the earthquake
swept through two villages, sending some houses sliding into the
sea and destroying about 100 others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
