<HEADLINE> Indonesia Sees Thomas/Uber Cups as Olympic Stepping-stone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
JAKARTA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's National Sports Council
(KONI) considers the Thomas and Uber Cups as the benchmark for its
goals in the Sydney Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
KONI Vice Chairman Arie Sudewo said Friday the players'
performance in the cups, badminton's premier team events, next
week would indicate their chances in the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
"I hope our men's and women's team will be able to achieve the
target of retaining the Thomas Cup for the 12th time and reaching
the semifinal of the Uber Cup. That will help us to win gold
medals in the Olympics," he was quoted by the Jakarta Post Friday
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia has targeted winning gold in at least the men's
singles and men's doubles at the Olympics from September 15 to
October 1.
</P>
<P>
Arie encouraged the players to win the Thomas/Uber Cups over
spectators through sportsmanship.
</P>
<P>
"Don't fear your opponents. You are on the same court with the
same conditions. All you have to do is do your best without
ignoring the values of sportsmanship. Shuttlers must be able to
maintain their condition, boost their fighting spirit and self-
confidence to win," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the International Badminton Federation issued the
list of 162 Olympic qualifiers on Wednesday. A total of 19
Indonesian shuttlers qualified for the event. 
</P>
</TEXT>
