<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Competitiveness Ranking Picks up: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand moved up a place from 34th
to 33rd in the latest competitiveness survey of 47 nations
conducted by the International Institute of Management Development
in Switzerland, The Thai government said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The institute was quoted by a Thai government report as saying
that Thailand had made a significant improvement during the past
year in the fields of educational investment, tourism and import
and export businesses.
</P>
<P>
However, the institute said that the country still lags behind
other countries in technological and telecommunications
development and the availability of computers.
</P>
<P>
Some Thai research bodies have urged the government to invest
more in scientific and technological research and development, and
liberalize the telecommunications sector.
</P>
<P>
Thailand used to command 29th place in the institute's
competitiveness ranking, but slipped to 39th place in 1998 before
moving up to 34th place last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
