<HEADLINE> Turkey to Hold Third Round of Voting for Presidency  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The third round of voting in
presidential election is set to be held in Turkey on Friday, during
which Ahmet Sezer is expected to be elected with high votes.
</P>
<P>
A total of six candidates, if there is no new withdrawal until
the election hour, will be competing in the third round.
</P>
<P>
Analysts predicted that Chief Judge of the Constitutional Court
Ahmet Sezer, who received 281 votes in the first round and 314
votes in the second round, will be elected in this round with more
than 400 votes.
</P>
<P>
The presiding judge who secured support from both within and
outside Parliament has so far won the most votes during the first
two rounds of balloting.
</P>
<P>
The Parliamentary General Assembly will convene at 3.00 p.m.
local time, and the deputies will cast their ballots in a secret
way.
</P>
<P>
Sezer is in outstanding advantage among the six contenders, the
rest of whom are Mail Buyukerman, independent Eskisehir Deputy;
Dogan Gures, Deputy of True Path Party (DYP); Sadi Somuncuoglu,
Deputy of Nationalist Movement Party (MHP); Nevzat Yalcintas,
Deputy of Virtue Party (FP); Rasim Zaimoglu, Deputy of DYP.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the Constitution, a candidate should get no
less than 276 votes in favor which is the simple majority of the
deputies, in the third round of voting to become the president.
</P>
<P>
In case of failure, two of the candidates who receive the
highest votes in this round, will attend the fourth round on May 9,
during which a candidate also should get 276 votes to win.
</P>
<P>
If a president is not elected in the fourth round, then the
parliament will be dissolved and new general elections be held. In
this event, incumbent President Suleyman Demirel will keep his post
until a new President is elected.
</P>
<P>
If Sezer is elected as the new president, he will take over the
presidency on May 16 when Demirel's term expires. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
