<HEADLINE> Russia Offers High-tech Transfer to Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Russia is offering the transfer
of high technology and expertise to Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Russia, renowned for its high-tech industries, is willing to
transfer its technology and help Malaysia develop its high-tech
industries, the Russian ambassador to Malaysia said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC) has big potential
and Russian scientists and companies could play a role in it,
Ambassador Alexey D. Zhoukov told a news conference here to
announce the 55th anniversary of Victory Day.
</P>
<P>
As part of Russia's efforts to promote its technology, about
100 Russian scientists and head of agencies attended a
presentation on the country's technology industries here last
month.
</P>
<P>
Russia is willing to send its scientists to serve with
Malaysian companies and government agencies, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador also said Russia is taking steps to increase its
direct trade with Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Several measures including joint development, trade missions
and reducing trade barriers are being initiated to boost trade
ties between the two countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Malaysia has quality electronic products but they are
being exported through other countries to Russia. 
</P>
