<HEADLINE> Thailand Joins Arabian Travel Market 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has taken part in a
tourism fair in the Middle East -- the Arabian Travel Market 2000
(ATM 2000), held in Dubai of the United Arab Emires (UAE) from May
2 and 5, according to a statement of the Tourism Authority of
Thailand (TAT) available here Friday.
</P>
<P>
TAT led entrepreneurs of 20 tourist-related firms to join the
ATM 2000, aimed to promote Thai tourism in the Middle East, as the
upward trend of Middle Eastern arrivals in Bangkok in the first
quarter of this year was observed, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
Over 175,000 Middle Eastern tourists visited Thailand in the
January-March period, an increase of 6.08 percent from the same
period of last year, with Israeli and UAE arrivals accounted for
the largest part, it added
</P>
<P>
The 20 tourist-related Thai firms, including hotels, travel
agents, and internet-based businesses, would exchange tourism
information, campaigns, and projects with their counterparts from
other countries, it stated.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Airways International Plc. (THAI), the national flag
carrier, had also cooperated with the TAT in supporting Thailand's
participation in the ATM 2000, along with its weekly flights to
the Middle East, as the Emires Airline of the UAE had also
provided daily flights to Bangkok to facilitate Middle Eastern
tourists, it said. 
</P>
