<HEADLINE> Macedonian, Serbian Chambers of Commerce Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A delegation from Yugoslavia's
Serbian Chamber of Commerce signed a cooperation agreement with
its Macedonian counterpart during a two-day visit in Skopje,
capital of Macedonia, reports reaching here said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The visit, the first to Macedonia by the Serbian Chamber of
Commerce, was aimed at promoting economic cooperation between the
two countries, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Macedonian Chamber of Commerce Dushan Petreski
and his Serbian counterpart Nedelko Suziq agreed that bilateral
economic cooperation has not reached the level where it should
have due to various reasons, including the impact of the Bosnian
War and lack of relevant agreements.
</P>
<P>
Petreski said he hoped the two government would conclude a free
trade agreement this year and improve bilateral trade conditions
while Suziq called for an early settlement of the visa issue to
facilitate Serbian businessmen in their travels to Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day visit which ended Thursday, Serbian
delegates met with representatives of Macedonian companies for
talks on cooperation in the fields of energy, metallurgy, chemical
industry, textile, agriculture and trade, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia was a republic of the former Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
