<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rain, Thunder Storms Kill 15 in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people have been confirmed
dead during the consecutive rainstorms in south China which also
caused 41.6 million yuan (five million U.S. dollars) of property
losses.
</P>
<P>
Eleven people died when houses collapsed due to the heavy rain.
A farmer was struck dead by stroke of lightning in the evening of
May 1. And another two people were whirled by floods and were
proved dead later.
</P>
<P>
More than 120,000 people in Guangdong Province have suffered
from the rainstorms which have caused land slide and collapse of
more than 900 houses.
</P>
<P>
Local governments and officials have participated in relief
work. The provincial government of Guangdong allocated one million
yuan for the storm-torn areas to build new shelters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
