<HEADLINE> MILF Declares Truce in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The separatist Moro Islamic
Liberation Front (MILF) has declared unilaterally a 48-hour truce
starting 6:00 a.m. Saturday (22:00 GMT, Friday) in all areas of
conflict in Mindanao, the official Philippine News Agency said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the agency, the declaration was contained in a one-
page document signed by Al Haj Murad, MILF's military chief, with
authorization from Hashim Salamat, the front's reclusive chieftain.
</P>
<P>
"The MILF hereby unilaterally declares a 48-hour truce in
Mindanao to give all concerned a chance to resolve peacefully the
Mindanao problem," said the MILF.
</P>
<P>
Edgardo Batenga, chief negotiator of the Philippine government,
said the government would welcome very much the latest development
but stressed that the government is yet to study its move
regarding the MILF's pronouncement.
</P>
<P>
On April 30, the MILF ordered all its forces in Mindanao to an
all-out war against government troops that resulted to six days of
conflict and bombings on several parts of the southern island.
</P>
<P>
The military said 161 MILF rebels, 20 soldiers and five
civilians were killed in six days of clashes while more than 100,
000 villagers fled their homes.
</P>
<P>
The MILF, the largest rebel group in the Philippines, has been
fighting for an independent state in Mindanao during the past two
decades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
