<TEXT>
<P>
SHENGYANG, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions on a
quarterly and annual basis. The ten regions include Guangdong,
Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang, Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing,
Tianjin, and Chongqing. These provinces and municipalities make up
the bulk of the Chinese economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the latest development in fixed assets
investment in Liaoning Province in northeast China in the first
quarter of the year:
</P>
<P>
Liaoning's investment in fixed assets reached 4.721 billion
yuan (569 million U.S. dollars) in January-March period, an
increase of 13.8 percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Investment in capital construction amounted to 1.763 billion
yuan (212 million dollars), up 29 percent, and that in real estate
sector, 820 million yuan (98.8 million dollars), up 33.9 percent
and investment in technical renovation, 1.838 billion yuan (221
million dollars), an increase of 51.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the province's investment in electronics,
posts and telecommunications and oil-processing industry also
increased. 
</P>
