<HEADLINE> Love Bug Virus Hits New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, May 5 (Xinhua) -- An international "love bug"
computer virus that has wreaked havoc on computer systems
worldwide in the past 24 hours hit New Zealand Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to a press released from New Zealand acting
Communications Minister Trevor Mallard, at least two government
departments' computer systems have been infected with the virus.
</P>
<P>
"The ministries of education and fisheries have been affected,
and the Department of Statistics has closed down its external e-
mail systems as a precaution," he said.
</P>
<P>
This is the most severe computer virus that has come to New
Zealand. The Evening Post, a Wellington-based newspaper, reported
that Wellington Newspapers LTD's computer system was struck with
the virus,the Ministry of Defense disconnected the Internet from
its internal computer system while seeking a remedy, and the State
Insurance was forced to close down its e-mail system.
</P>
<P>
In the press release, acting minister Mallard warned home
computer users not to open their e-mail packages until they have
received advice from their e-mail provider or have updated their
anti-virus protection software. 
</P>
