<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Massu Beats Third-Seeded Pozzi for Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
WASHINGTON, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Sixth-seeded Nicolas Massu of
Chile Thursday edged third-seeded Gianluca Pozzi of Italy 2-6, 6-2,
6-2 and moved up to the semifinals at the U.S. Men's Clay Court
Championships in Lake Buena Vista, Florida.
</P>
<P>
In another quarterfinal, Ramon Delgado of Paraguay defeated
Markus Hantschk of Germany 7-5, 6-4, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
The Pozzi-Massu match was between the only two seeded players
left in the draw and it pitted age and guile against youth and
power.
</P>
<P>
In the first set, Pozzi used varied spins and slices to Massu
and break the Chilean's serve in the first and fifth games.
</P>
<P>
Pozzi seemed to still be in control of the match when a series
of unforced errors cost him his serve at 1-3 in the second set.
The momentum of the match quickly shifted in favor of Massu, who
broke Pozzi again in the eighth game to take the set.
</P>
<P>
Playing aggressively from just inside the baseline, Massu put
pressure on a suddenly error-prone Pozzi, breaking the Italian's
serve to take a 3-1 lead in the final set, then secured his first
career ATP Tour semifinal berth by breaking Pozzi again in the
final game.
</P>
<P>
Delgado, playing in his first tournament since undergoing
surgery on his left knee last November, continued his unlikely run
to the semis, winning each set with a service break in the final
game.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
