<HEADLINE> China to Off Line Senior Sedan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, May 5 (Xinhua) -- China's major car producer in the
northeast will soon introduce its latest product of Hongqi
Flagship CA7460, an advanced sedan jointly developed with Ford
from the United States.
</P>
<P>
China First Automobile Group (CFAG), based in capital city of
Changchun in Jilin Province, has devoted to development of the
advanced sedan for four years and owns 100 percent of its
intellectual property right.
</P>
<P>
The Hongqi Flagship, 5.481 meters long and 1.98 meters wide,
will be the only domestic brand of its kind in China.
</P>
<P>
The CFAG plans to manufacture 100 Hongqi Flagship sedans this
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
