<HEADLINE> Agricultural Index of Major Chinese Regions: Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua is releasing dispatches on
major economic indicators of ten major Chinese regions on a
quarterly and annual basis. The ten regions include Guangdong,
Jiangsu, Shandong, Zhejiang, Henan, Liaoning, Shanghai, Beijing,
Tianjin, and Chongqing. These provinces and municipalities make up
the bulk of the Chinese economy.
</P>
<P>
The following is the agricultural situation in Henan Province
in central China, in the first quarter of the year:
</P>
<P>
Henan allocated some five million hectares of farmland for
summer grain crops this year, 40,000 hectares more than last year.
</P>
<P>
At present, parts of the province are hit by a severe drought.
</P>
<P>
During January and March, the province turned out 1.7 million
tons of meat, a 6.2 percent rise over the same period last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
