<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0015GMT, May 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- Rolls-Royce announced on Thursday new AE 3007 engine
business worth up to 59 million U.S. dollars following a decision
by Continental Express to convert options on 11 Embraer RJ 145
regional jets to firm orders.
</P>
<P>
Continental Express, the North American launch customer for the
ERJ 145, has now agreed to purchase 161 of the 50-passenger
aircraft and holds remaining options on an additional 39.
</P>
<P>
To date, Continental Express has received 61 ERJ 145s. It also
operates 10 37-passenger ERJ 135s, for which it still holds firm
orders for 40 and options on an additional 25 aircraft. (Rolls
Royce-Orders)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- An international donors' conference organized by the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP) and the Mozambique
government ended Thursday with a pledge to issue almost 453
million dollars over the next few months, much more than the
Maputo government initially requested to meet the cost of
reconstruction after disastrous flooding.
</P>
<P>
Italian Foreign Undersecretary Rino Serri said that the success
of the conference lay in "the great ability with which Mozambique
presented itself to the conference, with rigorous analyses and
very serious and well- founded proposals."
</P>
<P>
Serri recalled that Mozambique had seen economic recovery in
the '90s after a bloody civil war. It was therefore necessary now
to ensure "a rapid resumption of this positive course", without
neglecting other areas of Africa. (UN-Mozambique)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- The Inter-American Development Bank (IDB) on
Thursday granted Nicaragua a 10 million U.S. dollar loan to
modernize its tax revenue and customs systems.
</P>
<P>
The loan will serve to improve the technical and professional
capability of the Nicaragua Tax Administration and the Custom
Services Administration, reported Nicaragua state radio. (IDB-
Nicaragua-Grants)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
YANGON -- Opium production has declined significantly for three
consecutive years since 1997 with only 1,090 tons registered in
1999, 38 percent less than the previous year, said a Myanmar high-
ranking official.
</P>
<P>
Quoting a report of the survey jointly conducted by Myanmar and
the United States, Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, first secretary
of the Myanmar State Peace and Development Council, said the opium
production in the country in that year registered the lowest
within a 10-year period since 1988, official newspaper The New
Light of Myanmar reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, poppy cultivation areas have shrunk to 8,950
hectares in 1999, 31 percent less than the previous year, he said
at an annual meeting of the Myanmar Central Committee for Drug
Abuse Control on Thursday. (Myanmar-Drug)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- An international grain trading house in South
Africa is to export between 50,000 to 70,000 tons of South
African maize to Japan for delivery in July.
</P>
<P>
The South African Press Association quoted market sources as
saying on Thursday that the consignment would be a mix of yellow
and white maize with more yellow in the shipment than white. The
report, however, did not mention the name of the trading house. (
SAfrica-Japan-Export) 
</P>
</TEXT>
