<HEADLINE> School Bombed in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- A former Muslim mosque now serving as
an Arabic school for children was bombed around 1:20 a.m. Friday (
17:20 GMT, Thursday) in Davao city in the southern Philippines,
the local ABS-CBN television reported.
</P>
<P>
The TV report quoted witnesses as saying that a red pick-up
truck with a motorcycle back-up passed by the school seconds
before the actual bombing. No casualties were reported by the
television.
</P>
<P>
Police said the grenade was thrown to strike terror among
residents in wartorn Mindanao. A double red alert has been raised
among local police after the incident.
</P>
<P>
In nearby North Cotabato province, a bomb exploded in Carmen
town at around 11:00 p.m. (15:00 GMT) Thursday but caused no
casualties.Local authorities are still investigating what type of
bomb was used in the attack.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, an advance party sent by North
Catabato Governor Emmanuel Pinol to Aleosan was ambushed by still
unidentified rebels early Friday morning. At least five soldiers
were injured in the attack.
</P>
<P>
Philippine government troops have engaged in battles with two
rebel groups, the Abu Sayyaf and the Moro Islamic Liberation Front,
in the last few days in Mindanao. About 20 government soldiers and
more than 100 rebels were killed in the battles. 
</P>
