<HEADLINE> EU Qualifications Not to Be Lowered: French PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, May 4 (Xinhua) -- France supports the eastward
expansion of the European Union but the qualification terms for
candidate members would not be lowered to speed up the process,
said visiting French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference held after his talks with Hungarian
Prime Minister Orban Victor, Jospin said France will do its utmost
to accelerate the reforms inside the EU and its enlargement.
France takes over rotating EU presidency in July.
</P>
<P>
Jospin stressed that the EU's reforms will not affect the
process of its enlargement and that the EU will not make groups
among candidate members for their admission to the bloc, as the
process is a unified one, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Jospin reiterated France's support for the EU's political
sanctions against Austria, which has allowed the ultra-right
Freedom Party into the coalition government.
</P>
<P>
France and Hungary signed several agreements on environment
protection, technical exchanges and education during Jospin's two-
day visit.
</P>
<P>
Jospin, who arrived in Budapest on Wednesday, also held talks
with Hungarian President Goncz Arpad and Foreign Minister Martonyi
Janos.
</P>
<P>
France is the third largest investor and the fourth largest
trading partner of Hungary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
