<HEADLINE> Mad Dow Disease Found in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The daily of The Australian reported Friday that the Royal
Melbourne Hospital insisted Thursday to tell the nine the fact
though it could cause serious distress among them.
</P>
<P>
The nine patients were potentially exposed to the incurable
disease between April 20 and 28 after inadequately sterilized
equipment was used during neurosurgery. The equipment was used
earlier on a dementia patient, who had since been diagnosed as
possibly suffering from mad cow disease.
</P>
<P>
However, the paper said they face a wait of up to 30 years to
find out whether they have contracted the disease because there is
no accurate test for it prior to symptoms surfacing. 
</P>
