<DOCNO> XIE20000505.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chretien Meets Visiting Japanese Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien
met with visiting Japanese Prime Minister Yoshiro Mori here
Thursday morning on the preparedness of the upcoming G-8 summit.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders compared notes on the agenda for the summit
slated for July in Okinawa, Japan, according to the Canadian prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released by Chretien's press office, the prime
minister said he is strongly committed to the G-8 process, during
which he will be "working closely with Prime Minister Mori and
other G-8 colleagues to build a focused agenda for the next summit.
"
</P>
<P>
The day-long visit is part of Mori's seven-nation consultation
tour as current chairman of the G-8. The Japanese prime minister
arrived here after his brief visit in Britain Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mori, who had visited Russia, Italy, France and Germany, is yet
to meet with U.S. President Bill Clinton in Washington on the last
leg of his trip. 
