<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Has Two Plane Crashes in Two Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, May 5 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and six
others were injured when two aircraft crashed on Thursday and
Wednesday in Kazakhstan, said a report from the State Emergency
Situations Bureau.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday a Mi-8 helicopter, which belonged to a local
private aviation company, crashed in a mountain skiing sanitarium
in the outskirts of Alma Ata, capital of Kazakhstan. Of the 16
people on board, six were wounded, according to the bureau.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, a light sport plane crashed in its first test
flight near a village in Eastern Kazakhstan. The pilot, 51, was
found dead on the spot.
</P>
<P>
The reason of the two crashes were still under investigation by
the police, the bureau said. 
