<HEADLINE> Preliminary Round Ends at Ice Hockey Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 4 (Xinhua) -- Only Sweden and the Czech Republic
posted three straight wins during the preliminary round of the
64th Ice Hockey World Championship in St. Petersburg, Russia.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the round Thursday, Finland and the United States
emerged as the leaders of the other two groups.
</P>
<P>
In the four matches competed Thursday, Sweden crushed Belarus 9-
0, Italy beat Austria 3-0, Latvia defeated Ukraine 2-1. Finland
and Slovakia had a 2-2 tie.
</P>
<P>
Twelve of the 16 teams remained will be divided into two groups
to vie against each other in the qualification round from Friday
to next Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine, Austria, Japan and France, which were eliminated in
the preliminary round, will move to the consolatory round starting
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Russia, the host that lost two matches in the preliminary round,
has very dim hope of regaining its power status this time around.
</P>
<P>
Russia was the champion in 1993 but has not collected any medal
since then. 
</P>
