<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2100 GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Ahmet Necdet Sezer, presiding judge of the
Constitutional Court, was elected the 10th president of Turkey with
330 votes in the third round of balloting Friday.
</P>
<P>
He garnered three-fifths of the votes in the 550-seat
parliament, far more than the 276 votes required in the third round
to become the president.
</P>
<P>
As the joint candidate of the three ruling parties and two main
opposition parties represented in parliament, Sezer had been
considered the favorite for presidency and stood good chance to
win.(Turkey-Presidency)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli jet fighters on Friday bombed two power
stations in Lebanon and a guerrilla ammunition deport in
retaliation for a rocket attack by Lebanese Hezbollah on northern
Israel, the Israeli military said.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Beirut said the Israeli warplanes attacked early
Friday morning the power station of Bsalim on the outskirts of
Beirut and another station in Dier Amar, near the northern
Palestinian refugee camp of Beddawi.
</P>
<P>
The bombing also left a crater in the Damascus road near the
village of Tenayel, about 10 kilometers from the Syrian-
Lebanonborder.(Israel-Lebanon)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Katyusha rockets fired by Lebanese Hezbollah
guerrillas Friday struck Galilee Panhandle and other Israeli
northern areas for a second straight day, wounding several persons,
damaging properties and triggering fire.
</P>
<P>
Four waves of rockets landed in the areas, where local residents
just emerged from a night in their bomb shelters and went to market
for the weekend, according to Israel Radio reports. (Israel-
Lebanon-Guerrilla Attacks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Roed Larsen, envoy of the United Nations Secretary
General Kofi Annan, told a press conference here Friday that the U.
N. shares Lebanon's view the pro-Israel South Lebanon Army (SLA)
should be dismantled during the Israeli withdrawal process.
</P>
<P>
After his third round of meeting with Lebanese leaders, Larsen
stressed that Israel must "cease all communication with the SLA and
the Israeli-allied militia have to give up their heavy weapons."
(Lebanon-UN)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran holds the second round of the parliamentary
election Friday despite of the delay by the conservative Guardians
Council to confirm the first round result in Tehran constituency.
</P>
<P>
The polling started at 0900 a.m. (0430 GMT) in 52 constituencies
in 22 provinces. Some 132 candidates are running for the remaining
66 seats of the 290-seat Majlis (parliament).
</P>
<P>
The reformist allies of President Mohammad Khatami are believed
to repeat the landslide victory in the February polls though they
are deprived of a voice in the campaign after the conservative
judiciary closed down almost all the mouthpieces of the reformists.
(Iran-Parliamentary Runoffs) 
