<HEADLINE> Colombia Seizes Over One Ton of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The operation was carried out early Friday in the municipal
neighborhood of Cali, the capital of that department in the
southwest of Colombia. Twenty kilos of heroin, 500 million pesos (
250,000 dollars) in cash, and seven motor vehicles were captured
in the same action.
</P>
<P>
Colombian Police director General Rosso Jose Serrano traveled
to Cali after he learned of the results of the operation.
</P>
<P>
The seized cocaine would be sent to the United States and would
be put aboard a ship in the Buenaventura Port in the Pacific Ocean
littoral, near Cali. The drug arrived in Cali from the Putumayo
department jungles on the border with Ecuador.  
