<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Virus Hits 10,000 Computers in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 5 (Xinhua) -- The "I Love You" virus has hit up to 10,
000 computers in Italy and is still blocking systems at the Rome-
based United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization, experts
said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to early estimates from the information technology
security expert Fulvio Berghella, the impact of the virus in Italy
was not as devastating as in the United States where 60 percent to
80 percent of computers are said to have been infected.
</P>
<P>
Berghella said firms of all types and numerous individuals had
been hit by the virus, unable to resist the temptation of opening
a file with such an attractive name.
</P>
<P>
Anti-virus experts are at work all over Italy trying to repair
the damage caused by "I Love You", which destroys all files of a
certain length.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile at FAO all computers were down Friday, forcing it to
fall back on faxes and telephones to communicate with the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
