<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czechs Consolidate Lead in Ice Hockey Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 5 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Czech Republic
continued its lead Friday in the Ice Hockey World Champion
qualification match in St. Petersburg, chalking four straight wins.
</P>
<P>
The Czechs trounced Italy 9-2. They won seven goals in the
first two periods. Italy managed two goals in the third period.
</P>
<P>
Host Russia suffered another setback, losing to Latvia 2-3 and
moving even farther from its hope of ending its no-medal history
since 1993.
</P>
<P>
In other events Friday, Canada beat Finland 5-1 and the United
States defeated Belarus 1-0.
</P>
<P>
Four matches will be fought Saturday -- Sweden-Switzerland,
Slovakia-Norway, Ukraine-Japan, and Austria-France, the latter two
as part of the consolatory round among the four teams eliminated
in the preliminary round.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen teams are competing in the current championship, which
is scheduled to end on May 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
