<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe's Leading Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 5 (Xinhua) -- European stock markets rose at the
close of trading Friday with a fillip from strong advances on Wall
Street stocks and big gains from "new economy" stocks.
</P>
<P>
In London, the leading FTSE index posted a 39.2 points or 0.63
percent gain to end at 6238.8 points, down 88.6 on the week.
</P>
<P>
Telecom equipment maker Marconi was the best performer,surging
12.4 percent as investors took encouragement from a strong
earnings report by rival Alcatel Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Outsourcing firm Capita Group rose 7.5 percent.Vodafone
AirTouch and Scottish telecom firm Thus rose 3.3 percent and 3
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Europtop 300, a broad-based pan-European index, gained
0.1 percent, with oil and gas sectors rising more than 2 percent.
</P>
<P>
With technology and telecommunications shares leading the
market, Frankfurt's Xetra Dax index shot up almost 2 percent to
close at 7530.82, up 1 percent on last Friday's close.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the CAC 40 climbed 0.9 percent to 6548.09,with
technology shares leading the gains, some 7 percent up on the week.
</P>
</TEXT>
