<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rio Group To Get Closer to China, Russia: Colombian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pastrana said on occasion of the dinner offered to the foreign
ministers holding now the 19th Rio Group Foreign Ministers Meeting,
that he is going to promote a bigger rapprochement of the Group
with China and the Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
"We will promote for this the holding of a meeting of vice
foreign ministers with the Russian Federation, as well as a
meeting of the group's troika (Mexico, Colombia, and Chile) with
the Chinese government," he said.
</P>
<P>
The head of the Colombian state underscored in his speech the
importance of the group that represents 19 countries that occupy
more than 20 million square kilometers and that hold close to 500
million people of the planet.
</P>
<P>
Pastrana said that in his opinion, cooperation and frank
communication between the member countries are important to try to
unify the points of view on themes of common interests, which are
fundamental in the agenda of the new century.
</P>
<P>
The 19th Rio Group Foreign Ministers Meeting, attended by 19
member countries, was opened Friday morning in the Palace of San
Carlos, the Colombian Foreign Ministry's headquarters.
</P>
<P>
This is the first meeting of the Rio Group after its expansion
with the Central American countries and the Dominican Republic.
</P>
</TEXT>
